title: Add send_to_session agent tool for cross-session messaging
---
Add a new agent tool send_to_session that allows an agent in one session to send a message to another session's channel without waking the target agent. This is needed for cron-driven briefings to deliver results to a DM session.

Required parameters: session_id (string), message (string)
Optional parameters: wake_agent (bool, default false), store_in_history (bool, default true)

Internal infrastructure exists: inject_session_message_async in tools_builtin_util.ml already does cross-session injection (used for CI watch follow-ups). The new tool should expose this capability to agents.

Use cases: cron ephemeral sessions forwarding results to a persistent DM; postmortem notifications; background task completion alerts to a specific session.

Acceptance criteria:
1. send_to_session tool with session_id, message, wake_agent, store_in_history params
2. When wake_agent=false, message appears in channel but does not trigger agent loop on target session
3. When store_in_history=false, message is sent but not persisted in messages table
4. Error handling for unknown/invalid session keys
5. Rate limiting / abuse guard (max N cross-session sends per session per hour)
6. Wire into agent tool registry and agent template allowed_tools where appropriate